1
00:00:00,100 --> 00:00:05,011
Once a task passes the scorecard, the next job is to give the agent ground truth.

2
00:00:04,961 --> 00:00:14,019
A useful context package contains five things: the goal, the current state, the relevant files or systems, the constraints, and the definition of done.

3
00:00:14,019 --> 00:00:16,807
More context is not automatically better.

4
00:00:16,807 --> 00:00:21,384
The useful context is the smallest set that lets the agent act without guessing.

5
00:00:21,384 --> 00:00:23,798
Tool access should match the task.

6
00:00:23,798 --> 00:00:27,625
A document task may need a source folder and an output path.

7
00:00:27,625 --> 00:00:31,240
A data task may need a workbook plus validation rules.

8
00:00:31,240 --> 00:00:38,875
A publishing task may need an authenticated page, final copy, a thumbnail, and a clear instruction to stop before the publish button.

9
00:00:38,875 --> 00:00:41,028
Then design the feedback loop.

10
00:00:41,028 --> 00:00:48,663
The agent acts, reads the real result, compares it with the acceptance criteria, and either continues, repairs, or stops.

11
00:00:48,663 --> 00:00:51,923
This loop is what makes the path genuinely agentic.

12
00:00:51,923 --> 00:00:56,894
The plan can change from evidence, but it must not change from unsupported confidence.

13
00:00:56,894 --> 00:01:04,086
A test failure, missing source, invalid file, or provider rejection should become a new decision, not a detail to hide.

14
00:01:04,086 --> 00:01:07,000
Long work also needs visible checkpoints.

15
00:01:07,000 --> 00:01:13,442
Save intermediate artifacts, record tool results, preserve errors, and make the current state recoverable.

16
00:01:13,442 --> 00:01:19,413
A human should be able to see what changed, what remains, and why the agent believes the task is complete.

17
00:01:19,413 --> 00:01:21,644
This applies beyond software.

18
00:01:21,644 --> 00:01:26,259
A recruiting workflow can verify required fields and stop before outreach.

19
00:01:26,259 --> 00:01:30,480
A finance workflow can reconcile totals and surface exceptions.

20
00:01:30,480 --> 00:01:37,192
A content workflow can validate dimensions, chapters, and links before it asks for final publication approval.

21
00:01:37,192 --> 00:01:38,730
Chapter recap.

22
00:01:38,730 --> 00:01:45,759
First, package the smallest complete set of goal, state, context, constraints, and completion criteria.

23
00:01:45,759 --> 00:01:50,355
Second, make every important action return evidence that can change the plan.

24
00:01:50,355 --> 00:01:55,278
Third, preserve checkpoints so the work can be reviewed, resumed, and recovered.
